{"id":850,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":213,"title":"Cam7 - Test 2 - Part 1","subtitle":"Car Insurance Inquiry Call","level":"B1","parts":70,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam7-test-2-part-1.850/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/0-ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Hello... Motor Insurance Department...\nOh hello...\nI'd like to ask about insurance for my car.\nYes, of course.\nI'll just take a few details.\nWhat's your name?\nPatrick Jones.\nAnd your address?\nIt's 27 Bank Road.\n27 Bank Road.\nIs that in Greendale?\nYes.\nAnd what's your daytime phone number?\nMy work number is 730453.\nAnd could I ask what your occupation is?\nDentist.\nOkay...\nNow, a few details about your car...\nWhat size is the engine?\nIt's 1200 ccs.\nThank you...\nand the make and model?\nIt's a Hewton Sable.\nCould you spell the model name please?\nYes... SABLE.\nAh yes... thanks.\nAnd when was it made?\n1997.\nLovely...\nright...\nI presume you've had a previous insurer?\nYes.\nRight...\nwe need to know the name of the company.\nYes... it was Northern Star.\nThank you,\nand have you made any insurance claims in the last five years?\nYes...\none in 1999.\nAnd what was the problem?\nIt was stolen... but...\nThat's fine, Mr Jones... that's all we need to know at the moment...\nAnd will there be any other named drivers?\nJust the one...\nAnd his name?\nSimon Paynter.\nCould you spell the surname please?\nPAYNTER.\nOkay, thank you...\nAnd what relationship is he to you?\nHe's my brother-in-law.\nAnd what will you or Mr Paynter be using the car for?\nWell... uh... mainly for social use...\nWill you be using it to travel to work?\nYes... sometimes.\nAnything else?\nNo. That's it.\nAnd finally, when would you like to start the insurance?\nI'll need it from the 31st of January.\nRight...\nMr Jones... I'm getting a couple of quotes coming up on the computer now...\nand the best bet looks like being with a company called Red Flag.\nYeah.\nAnd that comes out at $450 per year...\nThat seems okay.\nIt's quite a bit lower than I've been paying up to now.\nGreat.\nSo, would you like me to go ahead with that?\nSure... why not?\nHow would you like to pay?","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:15","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Hello... Motor Insurance Department...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/1.mp3","time_start":0.69,"time_end":4.9},{"position":2,"content":"Oh hello...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/2.mp3","time_start":4.9,"time_end":5.87},{"position":3,"content":"I'd like to ask about insurance for my car.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/3.mp3","time_start":5.87,"time_end":8.7},{"position":4,"content":"Yes, of course.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/4.mp3","time_start":8.7,"time_end":10.15},{"position":5,"content":"I'll just take a few details.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/5.mp3","time_start":10.15,"time_end":12.46},{"position":6,"content":"What's your name?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/6.mp3","time_start":12.46,"time_end":13.97},{"position":7,"content":"Patrick Jones.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-2-part-1-2023-07-28-17-12-17/7.mp3","time_start":13.97,"time_end":15.5},{"position":8,"content":"And your address?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambr